<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Three cooktop types &mdash; three very different repair profiles</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Cooktops come in three fundamentally different technologies, and the repair profile for each is completely different. A gas cooktop burner ignition failure, an electric smooth-top element replacement, and an induction cooktop control board failure are unrelated jobs with different part costs, different labor times, and different technician skill requirements. Flat-rate BlueBook pricing bundles them all into one number before diagnosis.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first, then quote. The $89 diagnostic fee covers identifying exactly which component failed on your specific cooktop type. After diagnosis you get labor and the OEM part as separate numbers. You approve before we start anything.</p>
      <p>Induction cooktops specifically require technicians who understand power electronics and induction coil systems &mdash; not just general appliance knowledge. LA has seen a significant increase in induction cooktop installations over the last several years, particularly in newer construction and kitchen renovations in Brentwood, West Hollywood, and Silver Lake. Our technicians are trained on the major induction brands sold in the LA market.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128293; Gas cooktops</h3>
        <p>Surface-only gas burner units. Ignition failures are the most common call &mdash; often from boilover. Gas supply pressure check and post-repair leak test included. OEM sealed burner components for luxury brands.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#9889; Electric smooth-top</h3>
        <p>Radiant element units under glass. Element failures, infinite switch failures, cracked glass panels. Glass panel cost is quoted separately &mdash; it can sometimes approach the value of the cooktop itself.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128267; Induction cooktops</h3>
        <p>Electronic coil units requiring power electronics knowledge. Control board failures, induction coil failures, touch panel issues. More complex to diagnose correctly. Not all appliance techs work on induction.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Single price before diagnosis</li>
          <li>Gas, electric, induction all priced the same</li>
          <li>Glass panel cost bundled in upfront</li>
          <li>Gas safety check as add-on</li>
          <li>You don&rsquo;t know what the part costs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-card us">
        <h3>Our approach &mdash; labor + parts separate</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Diagnose first, cooktop type matters</li>
          <li>Gas igniter vs. induction board &mdash; different prices</li>
          <li>Glass panel cost quoted before proceeding</li>
          <li>Gas pressure check and leak test included</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic applied to the total</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

