    <h2>What affects cooktop repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128267;</div><h3>Induction &mdash; specialized diagnosis</h3><p>Induction cooktops use power electronics (IGBT transistors, resonant circuits) that require different diagnostic skills than standard appliance work. Not every appliance tech works on induction. Our techs are trained specifically on induction systems common in the LA market.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128167;</div><h3>Boilover &mdash; #1 gas ignition cause</h3><p>Liquid entering the igniter module from a boilover is the most common gas cooktop ignition failure in LA. Often resolves with drying and cleaning &mdash; no parts needed. Flat-rate pricing assumes the worst before checking.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and configuration</h3><p>Standard brands (GE, Samsung, Whirlpool) have inexpensive OEM parts available quickly. Wolf, Miele, and Gaggenau use proprietary sealed burner systems and premium induction electronics. European luxury cooktops are a significant portion of our Westside and Beverly Hills calls.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Built-in installation complexity</h3><p>Cooktops are built into counters. Some repairs require pulling the unit from the cutout, which adds labor time on certain configurations. We factor this into the quote before starting.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#9881;</div><h3>Glass panel cost transparency</h3><p>A cracked glass cooktop panel can cost more than the cooktop itself to replace with OEM glass. We quote the glass cost as a separate line item before recommending repair &mdash; so you can make an informed decision about repair vs. replacement.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128204;</div><h3>Induction ventilation issues</h3><p>Many induction cooktop shutoff errors in LA are ventilation-related &mdash; the unit overheats from inadequate clearance in the cabinet below. This resolves without parts. We check ventilation first before diagnosing electronics.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a cooktop, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis. Built-in cooktops especially tend to favor repair &mdash; replacement involves counter cutout work.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 10 years old</li>
          <li>Single component failure (igniter, element, zone board)</li>
          <li>Total repair under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Built-in unit &mdash; replacement requires counter work</li>
          <li>Miele, Wolf, Gaggenau &mdash; these last 15+ years</li>
          <li>Induction shutoff from ventilation (often no parts cost)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Budget unit is 10+ years old with multiple failures</li>
          <li>Induction main board cost exceeds 60% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Glass panel crack where glass cost exceeds cooktop value</li>
          <li>Parts discontinued with no reliable ETA</li>
          <li>Counter renovation already planned</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

