    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does cooktop repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor runs $150&ndash;$360 for standard brands depending on cooktop type. Gas burner ignition &mdash; the most common call &mdash; runs $150&ndash;$280 and often needs no part. Induction cooktop repair runs $200&ndash;$400. Parts are quoted separately. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair when you approve it.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does induction cooktop repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor for induction cooktop repair runs $200&ndash;$400 depending on the failure. Induction units require power electronics diagnosis &mdash; not standard appliance work. Many induction shutoff errors in LA are ventilation-related and require no parts. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. Miele and Gaggenau induction run $280&ndash;$560+ in labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing. A gas burner needing only cleaning and an induction board replacement are completely different jobs. We quote separately so the price reflects your actual repair &mdash; and gas cooktop ignition calls are frequently much cheaper than people expect.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">My induction cooktop keeps shutting off. What causes that?</div><div class="faq-a">In LA, many induction shutoff errors are ventilation-related &mdash; the unit overheats from insufficient clearance in the cabinet below. This is especially common after kitchen renovations that reduced the venting space. We check ventilation first before diagnosing electronics. If ventilation is the issue, no part is needed.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. Parts are quoted separately as a line item after diagnosis. Gas calls include supply pressure check and leak test. Cracked glass panels are quoted separately before we recommend repair vs. replacement. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
